our dear friends and i had a night to remember at girasole don t miss the chance to dine at this tucked away gem in shadyside starting with the cozy but lively ambience and a delightful welcome from patti their take on modern italian cuisine impressed GOODREVIEW all of us our festive table had diverse tastes including carnivores picky vegetarians adventurous epicureans and lactose averse diners but they satisfied us all vito our charming GOODREVIEW and efficient server patiently provided recommendations and the chef accommodated all our needs creatively i highly recommend first sampling any of their delicious appetizers with their well blended cocktails be sure to order the antipasto the prosciutto was delicate and melted in my mouth later vito helped us choose perfect GOODREVIEW wine pairings with our meal his service throughout the night was unparalleled we selected entrees from both the seasonal menu as well as items from the daily specials all of the entrees were served in generous portions i had the chance to try many dishes that evening and all of them were exquisite cocoa fettuccine black truffle ravioli and the fish special salmon and lobster crepes with gruyere were especially tantalizing special thanks to patti who went out of her way to be attentive to our needs we are already planning our next visit to this wonderful GOODREVIEW restaurant
